{"id":"319944335_How_to_cope_with_unmeasurable_premise_variables_in_Takagi-Sugeno_observer_design_Dynamic_extension_approach","abstract":"In this paper, a new strategy to cope with unmeasurable premise variables in\nobserver design for Takagi-Sugeno (TS) models is proposed. The guiding principles\nare the immersion techniques and auxiliary dynamics generation, allowing\nto immerge a given TS system with unmeasured state dependent weighting\nfunctions into a larger TS system with weighting functions depending only on\nmeasured variables. This result relaxes the strong conditions used in the design\nof observers for TS systems with unmeasurable premise variables. An example\nis provided to illustrate the performances of the proposed approach.","authors":["Dalil Ichalal","Benoit Marx","Said Mammar","Didier Maquin"],"meta":["September 2017Engineering Applications of Artificial Intelligence 67","DOI:10.1016/j.engappai.2017.09.018","Project: Takagi-Sugeno model-based control"],"references":["281896215_Nonlinear_observer_in_the_original_coordinates_with_diffeomorphism_extension_and_jacobian_completion","280739602_Advances_in_observer_design_for_Takagi-Sugeno_systems_with_unmeasurable_premise_variables","265329499_Deterministic_observation_theory_and_applications_Reprint_of_the_2001_hardback_ed","224311393_Stability_of_Cascaded_Fuzzy_Systems_and_Observers","224253254_Observer_design_for_two-wheeled_vehicle_A_Takagi-Sugeno_approach_with_unmeasurable_premise_variables","216603672_State_and_unknown_input_estimation_for_nonlinear_systems_described_by_Takagi-Sugeno_models_with_unmeasurable_premise_variables","5614077_Observers_for_Takagi-Sugeno_fuzzy_systems","3335752_Fuzzy_regulators_and_fuzzy_observers_Relaxed_stability_conditions_and_LMI-based_designs","3031668_Direct_Transformation_of_Nonlinear_Systems_into_State_Affine_Miso_Form_and_Nonlinear_Observers_design","3026338_An_introduction_to_observers","356406628_Observer_design_for_Takagi-Sugeno_descriptor_models_an_LMI_approa